CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 20, 1951, pg. 8, reads: "North Side YW Workers - When the new North Side Center of the Young Women's Christian Association opened at 100 West North Avenue last Thursday, these workers were on hand. Left to right: Joanne Peck, secretary; Mary Ruth Black, student staff member from the School of Social Work of the University of Pittsburgh; Ruth Henderson, director of the new North Side Center YWCA, and Mary Hall, assistant teen-age program director. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Joanne Peck, Mary Ruth Black, Ruth Henderson, and Mary Hall, standing in Northside YWCA
